      "id": "CVE-2023-5868",
      "source": "postgresql",
      "title": "Memory disclosure in aggregate function calls",
      "description": "test unsupported versions, but this problem is quite old.\nCertain aggregate function calls receiving \"unknown\"-type arguments could\ndisclose bytes of server memory from the end of the \"unknown\"-type value to the\nnext zero byte. One typically gets an \"unknown\"-type value via a string literal\nhaving no type designation. We have not confirmed or ruled out viability of\nattacks that arrange for presence of notable, confidential information in \ndisclosed bytes.",
      "severity": null,
      "cvss_score": null,
      "cvss_vector": null,
      "published_date": "2023-11-09",
      "modified_date": "",
      "affected": [],
      "references": [
