      "id": "CVE-2023-5870",
      "source": "postgresql",
      "title": "Role",
      "description": "test unsupported versions, but this problem is quite old.\nDocumentation says the\npg_signal_backend\nrole cannot signal \"a backend owned\nby a superuser\". On the contrary, it can signal background workers, including\nthe logical replication launcher. It can signal\nautovacuum\nworkers and the\nautovacuum\nlauncher. Signaling\nautovacuum\nworkers and those two launchers\nprovides no meaningful exploit, so exploiting this vulnerability requires a\nnon-core extension with a less-resilient background worker. Fo",
